-72; Lipson, D.A., Schmidt, S.K., Monson, R.K., Links between microbial population dynamics and nitrogen availability in an alpine ecosystem (1999) Ecology, 80, pp. 1623-1631; McKane, R.B., Rastetter, E.B., Shaver, G.R., Nadelhoffer, K.J., Giblin, A.E., Laundre, J.A., Chapin, F.S., Climatic effects on tundra carbon storage inferred from experimental data and a model (1997) Ecology, 78, pp. 1170-1187; Moorhead, D.L., Reynolds, J.F., Effects of climate change on decomposition in Arctic Tussock tundra: A modeling synthesis (1993) Arctic Alpine Res., 25, pp. 403-412; Myrold, D.D., Tiedje, J.M., Simultaneous estimation of several nitrogen cycle rates using 15N: Theory and application (1986) Soil Biol. Biochem., 18, pp. 661-665; Nadelhoffer, K.J., Giblin, A.E., Shaver, G.R., Linkins, A.E., Microbial processes and plant nutrient availability in arctic soils (1992) Arctic Ecosystems in a Changing Climate, , F.S. Chapin R.L. Jefferies J.F. Reynolds G.R. Shaver J. Svoboda E.W. Chu Academic Press; Nadelhoffer, K.J., Shaver, G.R., Giblin, A., Rastetter, E.B., Potential impacts of climate change on nutrient cycling, decomposition, and productivity in arctic ecosystems (1997) Global Change and Arctic Terrestrial Ecosystems, , W.C. Oechel T.V. Callaghan T. Gilmanov J.I. Holten B. Maxwell U. Molau B. Sveinbjörnsson Springer-Verlag New York; Oechel, W.C., Hastings, S.J., Vourlitis, G., Jenkins, M., Riechers, G., Grulke, N., Recent change of arctic tundra ecosystems from a net carbon dioxide sink to a source (1993) Nature, 361, pp. 520-523; Oechel, W.C., Vourlitis, G.L., Hastings, S.J., Zulueta, R.C., Hinzman, L., Kane, D., Acclimation of ecosystem CO2 exchange in the Alaskan Arctic in response to decadal climate warming (2000) Nature, 406, pp. 978-981; Post, W.M., Emanuel, W.R., Zinke, P.J., Stangenberger, A.G., Soil carbon pools and world life zones (1982) Nature, 298, pp. 156-159; Schimel, D.S., Braswell, B.H., Holland, E.A., McKeown, R.D., Ojima, S., Painter, T.H., Parton, W.J., 